children.text: There is evidence that the temporary fasteners have not been installed to support the plasterboard on every second wall stud.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
The wall sheet manufacturer’s installation manual states
‘temporary fasteners (nails or screws driven through plasterboard blocks to hold sheets in place while adhesive cures) must be installed at every second stud and remain for at least 24 hours’ .
The builder should either replace the affected wall sheeting, or provide documentation from the manufacturer that the method used will be appropriate.
